10
00:01:34,710 --> 00:01:35,610
Hari Om Tat Sat.

11
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:37,050
Namaste to everyone.

12
00:01:39,790 --> 00:01:41,330
My name is Satchitananda.

13
00:01:41,490 --> 00:01:45,930
I recognize some of you, and there are
some new faces here today as well.

14
00:01:51,610 --> 00:01:56,230
My sincere gratitude for making time to
come to this presentation.

15
00:02:02,010 --> 00:02:08,630
For any of us who are exploring anything
deeply, you know how valuable it is to be

16
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:10,930
able to reflect that information.

17
00:02:17,610 --> 00:02:19,630
To reflect that information.

18
00:02:24,030 --> 00:02:28,530
As part of the process of digestion and
integration.

19
00:02:33,210 --> 00:02:44,230
I am a yoga practitioner for over two
decades now, and have also gone deep into

20
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:48,910
other modalities like Shaolin Kung Fu.

21
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:59,850
Lots of time in nature, and lots of time
in the office with the laptop as well.

22
00:03:04,990 --> 00:03:13,230
I only mention that to say that this talk
will hopefully be an integration of my

23
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:13,970
background.

24
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:27,050
And as such, will hopefully present
something in a different perspective than

25
00:03:27,050 --> 00:03:29,270
you may have encountered before.

26
00:03:35,110 --> 00:03:43,030
Most of all, I hope that you feel inspired
to create models of understanding that

27
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:46,830
feel real and practical to your life.

28
00:03:55,630 --> 00:04:02,530
It's taken me about twenty-five years of
exposure to this information.

29
00:04:10,470 --> 00:04:14,190
And a couple of big waves in life.

30
00:04:25,970 --> 00:04:38,030
To make the Vidya accessible in a way that
really makes a difference to positivity in

31
00:04:38,030 --> 00:04:38,750
my life.

32
00:04:46,490 --> 00:04:50,710
My main training in yoga is from
Satyananda Yoga.

33
00:04:54,310 --> 00:04:59,210
But I'm not a representative of the ashram
in any way, and that also gives me the

34
00:04:59,210 --> 00:05:01,930
freedom to speak my thoughts freely.

35
00:05:08,430 --> 00:05:13,330
If there's something you disagree with,
or you feel isn't a version you've heard,

36
00:05:13,610 --> 00:05:18,770
please know that's my version,
and you can go to the ashram to get the

37
00:05:18,770 --> 00:05:20,050
original version.

38
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:24,710
If there's something you disagree with,
or you feel isn't a version you've heard,

39
00:05:24,710 --> 00:05:28,470
please know that's my version,
and you can go to the ashram to get the

40
00:05:28,470 --> 00:05:29,210
original version.

41
00:05:29,210 --> 00:05:31,650
We'll be doing a few practices.

42
00:05:32,130 --> 00:05:37,670
As with all practices, I don't know your
background, so you have the option to just

43
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:39,630
watch, rather than participate.

44
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,750
You got distracted?

45
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,660
All practices are optional.

46
00:06:02,980 --> 00:06:05,860
Be reasonable in anything you do.

47
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,960
Everything will be very basic this
evening.

48
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:17,480
I also like to make comments on psychology
and physiology.

49
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:24,780
I'm not a registered psychologist or a
doctor.

50
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:27,860
No es doctor, recibido, ni psicólogo.

51
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:35,680
Así que los invito a que cualquier duda lo
verifiquen.

52
00:06:43,490 --> 00:06:46,180
Entonces vamos a empezar con el Shantipat.

53
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:53,060
Shantipat is a way for all of us to just
sink in, independent of where we came from

54
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:54,000
this evening.

55
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:01,940
So please bring yourself into a
comfortable sitting position.

56
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:10,380
Ideally where the legs provide a stable,
balanced base.

57
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:21,280
For the spine, neck and head.

58
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:24,540
Spine comfortably upright.

59
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:31,900
Neck balanced on the shoulders.

60
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,740
Head balanced on the neck.

61
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:54,920
Arms relaxed and the hands optionally in a
mudra.

62
00:07:55,240 --> 00:08:05,140
A simple one is to touch the tips of the
index fingers to the thumb.

63
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:09,420
If comfortable, eyes gently closed.

64
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:14,460
Los ojos cómodamente y suavemente
cerrados.

65
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:16,040
As well as the mouth.

66
00:08:25,060 --> 00:08:29,520
Sit with yourself and give time to settle
within your body.

67
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:38,020
Siéntese con ustedes mismos y denle tiempo
al cuerpo para que se asienten.

68
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:51,940
En este proceso está bueno sentir las
partes principales del cuerpo.

69
00:08:56,420 --> 00:09:00,100
Especialmente aquellas partes que están en
contacto con el suelo.

70
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:05,500
Las partes que se tocan unas con otras.

71
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:13,340
Y las partes que están en contacto con el
aire.

72
00:09:20,540 --> 00:09:28,000
As you become aware of any body part,
add that to the mental image of how you're

73
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:32,920
sitting right now.

74
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:44,600
Try and create a complete visualization of
how you're sitting by actually feeling

75
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,340
that part.

76
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:50,500
Completa visualización de cómo están
sentados.

77
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:06,940
Notice that within the stillness of the
body, the breath is moving on its own.

78
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:12,800
Sea consciente de que a medida que el
cuerpo se va quietando, la respiración

79
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:15,400
igual se va moviendo en forma
independiente.

80
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:21,420
Without feeling the need to change it,
notice where it can be felt, how deep.

81
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:28,900
Sin necesidad de modificarla, la
respiración, sientan en qué parte del

82
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:31,400
cuerpo se siente y cuán profunda es.

83
00:10:47,540 --> 00:10:53,200
In this process of internalization,
it's very common for impressions of the

84
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,620
day or the week to present themselves.

85
00:10:55,960 --> 00:11:00,580
En este proceso de internalización,
es muy probable que vengan imágenes de

86
00:11:00,580 --> 00:11:03,260
hechos que sucedieron en el día o durante
la semana.

87
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:07,260
There's no conflict with the mind at this
point.

88
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:17,340
But it can be really helpful to just step
back and be the witness of any mental

89
00:11:17,340 --> 00:11:17,980
activity.

90
00:11:27,340 --> 00:11:31,300
And whenever possible, come back to
following the breath in and out of

91
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:31,720
yourself.

92
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:38,260
Vuelvan a concentrarse en la respiración y
a seguir a ver cómo estaban respirando.

93
00:12:03,540 --> 00:12:07,820
Empiecen a profundizar en la respiración,
a hacerla más profunda en las dos

94
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:08,460
direcciones.

95
00:12:12,140 --> 00:12:15,780
Muy de a poco, pero progresivamente.

96
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:29,260
De manera tal que cada nueva respiración
sea un poquito más profunda que la

97
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:30,940
anterior en las dos direcciones.

98
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:58,600
Y a esta respiración le vamos a agregar un
foco mental.

99
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:11,420
Un circuito imaginario desde el ombligo al
esternón y a la garganta.

100
00:13:12,060 --> 00:13:20,780
Pueden imaginarlo como una vía del tren o
como un tubo.

101
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:31,920
De manera tal que a medida que van
respirando, van sintiendo cómo el aire

102
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:35,560
sube a través del ombligo hasta la
garganta.

103
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:47,220
Y cuando exhalan, van sintiendo cómo la
respiración baja desde la garganta,

104
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:49,380
esternón y ombligo.

105
00:13:59,140 --> 00:14:07,770
Pueden visualizar este movimiento como una
luz o como una sensación.

106
00:14:13,490 --> 00:14:19,930
Cualquier técnica que le ayude a la mente
a mantenerse conectada con la respiración.

107
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:28,370
Moviéndose hacia arriba y hacia abajo en
este pasaje psíquico frontal.

108
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:48,040
Y con la próxima inhalación sigan
haciéndose recorrido que pase a través de

109
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:50,560
la garganta y siga hasta el entresejo.

110
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:59,840
Y ahora empiecen a respirar hacia adentro
y hacia afuera por el entresejo.

111
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:10,720
Es como si la inhalación perforara el
entresejo y se mueve hasta el centro del

112
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,120
cerebro.

113
00:15:18,180 --> 00:15:22,000
Sintiendo esa región de la cabeza que se
llena de prana, de vitalidad.

114
00:15:27,740 --> 00:15:29,820
Y al exhalar, sientan que la respiración
baja de la garganta.

115
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:36,280
La respiración y la atención se mueven
desde el centro del cerebro a través del

116
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,780
entresejo hacia el exterior.

117
00:15:56,410 --> 00:16:04,790
Y ahora dejen que la mente se estabilice
al punto del entresejo, en el punto del

118
00:16:04,790 --> 00:16:07,270
entresejo, se enfoque en el punto del
entresejo.

119
00:16:09,630 --> 00:16:16,870
La forma de una llama dorada.

120
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:23,190
Visualicen la forma, el color.

121
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:28,310
Pueden hasta sentir el calor.

122
00:16:34,310 --> 00:16:40,010
Y si no aparece ninguna imagen,
mantengan la idea de que hay una luz en

123
00:16:40,010 --> 00:16:40,610
ese punto.

124
00:16:47,790 --> 00:16:53,670
Y concentrados en esta luz interior,
cantamos tres veces el mantra OM.

125
00:16:56,350 --> 00:17:02,490
Y los chanti mantras de apertura,
todos juntos también.

126
00:17:09,170 --> 00:17:16,350
Y si no estás familiarizado con los
mantras, escuchá el sonido y sentí cómo

127
00:17:16,350 --> 00:17:18,090
vibran en ti.

128
00:17:21,590 --> 00:17:23,350
Respiramos lento y profundo.

129
00:18:54,110 --> 00:18:57,730
Frote las palmas una con la otra,
esto se llama palming.

130
00:18:58,290 --> 00:19:03,550
La idea es crear calor entre las palmas.

131
00:19:07,450 --> 00:19:14,510
Y cuando tengan ese calor, posan sobre los
ojos y comparten el calor con los ojos.

132
00:19:18,250 --> 00:19:22,690
Y sean conscientes de lo que ven en ese
espacio oscuro.

133
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:33,450
Y después con una inhalación, expandan ese
calor en ustedes mismos.

134
00:19:33,450 --> 00:19:37,130
Y mientras exhalan, bajan las manos.

135
00:19:40,530 --> 00:19:55,270
Esta práctica de Shantipat para mí es un
ejemplo de la genialidad de Swami

136
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:56,010
Satyananda.

137
00:19:56,290 --> 00:20:03,430
Para los que no lo conocen, es el
individuo en la parte derecha de la archa.

138
00:20:03,450 --> 00:20:05,290
¿Qué es lo que se llama ahí de la derecha?

139
00:20:13,110 --> 00:20:19,690
Una práctica simple del Shantipat hace que
la conciencia rote a través de todos los

140
00:20:19,690 --> 00:20:20,130
koshas.

141
00:20:33,450 --> 00:20:44,290
Para que cada parte del cuerpo que
queremos, de nosotros mismos, que queremos

142
00:20:44,290 --> 00:20:51,010
conocer un poco más en profundidad,
tiene que ser repetida miles de veces.

143
00:20:56,830 --> 00:21:01,830
Porque dice que toma mucho tiempo
profundizar y hacer una conexión genuina

144
00:21:01,830 --> 00:21:02,990
con esa parte.

145
00:21:11,310 --> 00:21:16,730
Y hace que el tiempo de repetirlo,
es el tiempo que se tarda, que se necesita

146
00:21:16,730 --> 00:21:18,190
para crear esa conexión.

147
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:25,610
Cada uno de nosotros somos expertos en
nuestra área de conocimiento.

148
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:42,250
Y cuando ponemos el foco, le damos control
a ese entorno, a ese espacio, esa parte es

149
00:21:42,250 --> 00:21:44,330
como que realmente empieza a brillar.

150
00:21:47,230 --> 00:21:51,490
Pero afuera de ese entorno que no tenemos
control,

151
00:22:04,630 --> 00:22:06,590
no le cuesta mucho la vida voltear.

152
00:22:11,650 --> 00:22:13,890
¿Y usted se siente identificado con esto?

153
00:22:20,430 --> 00:22:26,590
Dice que con un poco de práctica,
él se puede meter en sus sueños y trabajar

154
00:22:26,590 --> 00:22:28,470
en su inconsciente.

155
00:22:34,270 --> 00:22:41,870
Cuando tiene que cantar mantras frente a
500 personas en el ashram, dice que se

156
00:22:41,870 --> 00:22:44,950
duerme y cabecea el micrófono.

157
00:22:52,250 --> 00:22:57,390
Eso es la parte opuesta de que cada uno
nos vivimos.

158
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:07,350
Podemos ser unos psicólogos expertos,
aconsejar a otros para arreglar

159
00:23:07,350 --> 00:23:15,730
relaciones, y podemos no saber cómo hablar
con nuestra pareja o con nuestros hijos.

160
00:23:19,490 --> 00:23:21,850
Y cada uno puede encontrar sus propios
ejemplos en la vida.

161
00:23:31,650 --> 00:23:34,990
Repetir algo muchas veces es como que
termina estableciendo una conexión,

162
00:23:40,470 --> 00:23:45,430
entonces empieza a haber menos contraste
entre un ambiente controlado y un ambiente

163
00:23:45,430 --> 00:23:46,110
espontáneo.

164
00:23:46,210 --> 00:23:52,530
Esa es la motivación para un yogi y para
una yogi.

165
00:23:57,390 --> 00:24:00,610
Esta es la motivación para cualquiera que
quiera explorar en la conciencia.

166
00:24:05,150 --> 00:24:08,550
Esta es la motivación para cualquiera que
quiera explorar en la Tierra.

167
00:24:08,810 --> 00:24:10,670
Los océanos.

168
00:24:10,930 --> 00:24:13,870
El espacio.

169
00:24:14,230 --> 00:24:19,130
Puede ser el espacio externo o el espacio
interior.

170
00:24:24,190 --> 00:24:30,170
Y cada exploración requiere entender las
leyes de cada una de esas realidades.

171
00:24:30,390 --> 00:24:32,530
Y esas leyes no son simples.

172
00:24:37,530 --> 00:24:42,570
Hemos venido estudiando física por dos mil
años,

173
00:24:45,990 --> 00:24:49,110
y siguen apareciendo nuevas capas.

174
00:24:57,690 --> 00:25:01,990
Cada capa que vamos descubriendo nos va
dando una nueva dimensión de la realidad

175
00:25:01,990 --> 00:25:03,290
que nos sigue sorprendiendo.

176
00:25:03,870 --> 00:25:08,970
La promesa es que existen muchos tesoros
adentro de muchos espacios.

177
00:25:10,250 --> 00:25:19,110
La promesa es que existen muchos tesoros
adentro de muchos espacios.

178
00:25:22,910 --> 00:25:27,370
Y como cada buscador de tesoros,
está bueno tener un mapa.

179
00:25:30,590 --> 00:25:35,290
Y por supuesto que sea preciso el mapa,
que es mucho mejor que un mapa no preciso.

180
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:39,930
Al principio como que confiamos en otros.

181
00:25:44,110 --> 00:25:47,710
Y al principio como que queremos tomar
nota para armar nuestro propio mapa.

182
00:25:49,130 --> 00:25:54,250
Y el tema de hoy es el tema de hoy.

183
00:25:54,570 --> 00:26:06,930
Es un mapa bastante rústico de nuestro
mundo interno.

184
00:26:07,150 --> 00:26:13,210
De lo que vamos a atravesar cinco.

185
00:26:14,650 --> 00:26:16,990
Pero ese número es arbitrario.

186
00:26:19,130 --> 00:26:25,770
Estas no son líneas difíciles,
bien delimitadas.

187
00:26:25,950 --> 00:26:34,370
Son como sensaciones que se sobreponen e
interactúan.

188
00:26:34,910 --> 00:26:47,810
Son como una profundización en especial de
tres capas que son las que están más

189
00:26:47,810 --> 00:26:48,950
elevadas, más altas.

190
00:26:53,890 --> 00:26:57,070
Y puede profundizar en cada una de estas
cinco capas.

191
00:26:59,650 --> 00:27:02,810
Y eso es lo que hemos hecho como personas,
como seres humanos.

192
00:27:06,390 --> 00:27:09,650
Hay gente que se siente como distante,
cold.

193
00:27:12,270 --> 00:27:13,330
Ah, un chamago.

194
00:27:19,130 --> 00:27:25,170
Entonces a esas temas que están como
llamados, le dan como una atención

195
00:27:25,170 --> 00:27:25,750
especial.

196
00:27:30,530 --> 00:27:32,130
No quiero olvidarme de decir...

197
00:27:38,070 --> 00:27:44,130
Y si durante esta charla se ven atraídos o
les llama la atención alguna de estas

198
00:27:44,130 --> 00:27:45,130
capas...

199
00:27:49,710 --> 00:28:03,970
Y no han encontrado el llamado que la vida
los llama, o el suadharma...

200
00:28:03,970 --> 00:28:09,790
Entonces estén atentos a si sienten algún
llamado porque eso puede ser algo que les

201
00:28:09,790 --> 00:28:11,670
llame la atención para poder profundizar.

202
00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:34,550
Y no dejen

203
00:28:38,990 --> 00:28:50,990
pasar esa oportunidad, esa posibilidad.

204
00:28:53,570 --> 00:28:56,250
We're going to do a small practice.

205
00:28:58,570 --> 00:28:59,490
Lying down.

206
00:29:01,610 --> 00:29:06,370
I'm going to be asking you to rotate your
awareness in different areas.

207
00:29:09,910 --> 00:29:12,050
There is really nothing else to do.

208
00:29:14,850 --> 00:29:20,490
Even if the translation sometimes has a
pause, don't worry about it.

209
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:22,390
Just keep listening passively.

210
00:29:27,550 --> 00:29:31,170
Head facing this way, feet facing the
other way.

211
00:29:41,090 --> 00:29:41,870
You're doing great.

212
00:29:44,790 --> 00:29:50,230
Sometimes I lose the beginning.

213
00:29:51,870 --> 00:29:57,750
You want to make your body as straight as
possible in the spine.

214
00:30:00,510 --> 00:30:02,710
Spine as straight as possible.

215
00:30:07,450 --> 00:30:11,330
The feet are hip to shoulder width apart.

216
00:30:11,870 --> 00:30:14,290
Rolling outwards as comfortable.

217
00:30:21,910 --> 00:30:24,310
Palms turned upwards.

218
00:30:27,150 --> 00:30:30,150
Back of the head balanced along the
midline.

219
00:30:32,850 --> 00:30:35,510
Back of the head balanced along the
midline.

220
00:30:43,570 --> 00:30:49,630
Keep checking into your body parts and
find a way to release the weight of them

221
00:30:49,630 --> 00:30:50,550
onto the floor.

222
00:30:58,290 --> 00:31:03,410
If you have any glasses on or anything
tight around the waist or hair,

223
00:31:03,650 --> 00:31:04,970
that can also be removed.

224
00:31:14,290 --> 00:31:20,210
Right at this moment, check into how you
feel physically.

225
00:31:26,070 --> 00:31:32,490
Any body parts that may have been talking
to you or are talking to you right now.

226
00:31:37,550 --> 00:31:40,670
Notice how you feel energetically.

227
00:31:46,810 --> 00:31:52,490
Are you feeling tired and could stay in
this position for the next few hours?

228
00:31:58,370 --> 00:32:03,290
Or feeling energetic and would like to run
a few laps?

229
00:32:07,030 --> 00:32:08,330
Or somewhere in the middle?

230
00:32:15,390 --> 00:32:21,390
When you're with yourself in this state of
stillness, is the mind loud or quiet?

231
00:32:30,150 --> 00:32:35,930
Is it happy to notice what's in the
present moment or is there something it's

232
00:32:35,930 --> 00:32:37,830
going to in the past or future?

233
00:32:42,350 --> 00:32:45,570
There is no judgment either way.

234
00:32:45,730 --> 00:32:48,390
Really be the detached observer.

235
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:07,340
Are there any deep feelings that you're
aware of carrying inside you?

236
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:26,800
Any life situations you've recently found
a solution for?

237
00:33:30,100 --> 00:33:33,420
Or that you continue to be challenged by?

238
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:49,780
And underlying any movements of the breath
or the mind?

239
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:10,620
Can you contact that part of you that's
always the same?

240
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:26,480
That part of you that is the essence of
you.

241
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:34,500
That part of you that even at this moment
silently repeats, I am.

242
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:42,940
I am here.

243
00:34:44,740 --> 00:34:46,580
I am conscious.

244
00:34:54,410 --> 00:35:02,090
If there is any positive sentence you use
in your life, this is the time to repeat

245
00:35:02,090 --> 00:35:02,970
it mentally.

246
00:35:02,970 --> 00:35:09,690
And if you have any sentence, any prayer,
any positive resolution you use in your

247
00:35:09,690 --> 00:35:11,970
life, this is a good time to repeat it.

248
00:35:18,910 --> 00:35:25,590
Any sentence or prayer that somehow
manifests any deep transformation you want

249
00:35:25,590 --> 00:35:25,970
to achieve.

250
00:35:33,570 --> 00:35:41,270
And if you don't have that sentence,
you can visualize an ideal situation of

251
00:35:41,270 --> 00:35:41,810
yourself.

252
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:07,440
We are going to move our attention between
the different layers, the different layers

253
00:36:07,440 --> 00:36:10,120
of our being.

254
00:36:14,660 --> 00:36:18,800
And we start with the physical body or
Annamaya Kosha.

255
00:36:24,340 --> 00:36:31,920
And when you hear the name of a part of
the body, bring your attention to that

256
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:32,480
