Right chest.

353
00:41:02,540 --> 00:41:04,060
Left chest.

354
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:06,780
Chest center.

355
00:41:08,340 --> 00:41:09,320
Upper abdomen.

356
00:41:11,620 --> 00:41:12,180
Navel.

357
00:41:13,540 --> 00:41:14,600
Lower abdomen.

358
00:41:17,300 --> 00:41:18,380
Pubic bone.

359
00:41:20,220 --> 00:41:21,120
Pelvic floor.

360
00:41:22,820 --> 00:41:26,120
Check into your current state of
consciousness.

361
00:41:30,140 --> 00:41:35,260
If the mind has entered sleep,
remain connected to the voice.

362
00:41:39,820 --> 00:41:42,780
Feel into the whole right leg and foot.

363
00:41:46,780 --> 00:41:48,780
The whole left leg and foot.

364
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:53,320
Both legs and feet.

365
00:41:56,140 --> 00:41:57,620
Right arm and hand.

366
00:42:01,560 --> 00:42:03,620
The whole left arm and hand.

367
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:09,290
Both arms and hands as one.

368
00:42:14,700 --> 00:42:15,700
Back of torso.

369
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:19,640
Front of torso.

370
00:42:21,820 --> 00:42:23,540
The whole torso.

371
00:42:25,500 --> 00:42:26,260
Neck.

372
00:42:28,500 --> 00:42:30,000
Head and face.

373
00:42:32,180 --> 00:42:34,220
The neck, head and face together.

374
00:42:39,520 --> 00:42:42,080
Experience the whole right half of the
body.

375
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,420
The whole left half of body.

376
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:54,260
Experience the whole body at the same
time.

377
00:42:56,660 --> 00:43:02,820
Be aware of which body parts are within
and outside the field of awareness.

378
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:13,820
And bring awareness into those areas where
it is not.

379
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:23,900
Deepening into the experience of full body
awareness.

380
00:43:29,960 --> 00:43:34,380
From the inside of the bones to the
surface of the skin.

381
00:43:58,920 --> 00:44:01,920
And now we move into the Pranic dimension.

382
00:44:05,860 --> 00:44:07,340
The Pranamaya Kosha.

383
00:44:09,740 --> 00:44:14,160
Within the stillness of the body,
feel for signs of life.

384
00:44:20,420 --> 00:44:24,600
The beating of the heart and circulation
of blood.

385
00:44:38,060 --> 00:44:42,880
Any digestion and metabolism of energy.

386
00:44:54,260 --> 00:44:58,460
Sensations of warmth or coolness in the
body.

387
00:45:08,990 --> 00:45:11,410
Movements of the natural breath.

388
00:45:34,050 --> 00:45:40,050
With each breath out, follow the breath
from the sternum to out the nasal

389
00:45:40,050 --> 00:45:40,830
passages.

390
00:45:42,330 --> 00:45:50,130
With each breath out, follow the breath
from the sternum to out the nasal

391
00:45:50,130 --> 00:45:50,450
passages.

392
00:45:51,350 --> 00:46:00,130
This is the pathway of Prana, the upward
moving vital force.

393
00:46:16,980 --> 00:46:23,800
Now with each breath in, feel it move from
navel down to pelvic floor.

394
00:46:31,520 --> 00:46:45,440
This is the region of Apana, the downward
moving vital force.

395
00:47:04,240 --> 00:47:11,000
Shift the awareness to the navel and
imagine a side to side movement with each

396
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:11,000
breath.

397
00:47:11,020 --> 00:47:20,960
Now shift the attention to the navel and
imagine a side to side movement with each

398
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:20,960
breath.

399
00:47:22,940 --> 00:47:29,800
The region of Samana Prana.

400
00:47:36,270 --> 00:47:38,710
Relaxed body, open mind.

401
00:47:44,950 --> 00:47:50,930
Feeling for anything that feels like the
movement of energy described.

402
00:48:00,290 --> 00:48:04,770
Place the awareness now through the legs
and arms.

403
00:48:09,230 --> 00:48:13,190
The area of Udana, vital force.

404
00:48:20,600 --> 00:48:24,260
Any movements you are aware of through the
legs and arms.

405
00:48:31,580 --> 00:48:37,140
In the form of the subtlest sensation you
are aware of in those regions.

406
00:48:46,020 --> 00:48:53,260
And finally, feel for an energy that
pervades the whole body.

407
00:49:00,440 --> 00:49:02,120
Vyana Prana.

408
00:49:04,760 --> 00:49:10,260
It is the reservoir or buffer vital force.

409
00:49:19,710 --> 00:49:20,790
We

410
00:49:30,220 --> 00:49:35,080
now move our awareness through the parts
of the mind.

411
00:49:41,080 --> 00:49:48,600
Starting with Manas or perception and
cognition.

412
00:49:51,300 --> 00:49:54,120
Become aware of body parts and mind.

413
00:49:54,140 --> 00:49:56,020
Move your attention in contact with the
floor.

414
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:08,280
Move your mind to the most predominant or
strongest sensation.

415
00:50:15,040 --> 00:50:19,740
Stay there for some time, then find the
next most predominant sensation.

416
00:50:28,900 --> 00:50:32,360
Specifically, sensation of touch.

417
00:50:59,500 --> 00:51:03,020
Now include the top surface of the body as
well.

418
00:51:08,900 --> 00:51:13,280
Continue to move the mind from sensation
to sensation.

419
00:51:28,220 --> 00:51:31,420
We move to Buddhi or the intellect.

420
00:51:35,020 --> 00:51:37,100
Imagine a square.

421
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:47,200
Place a dot at the center of each line of
that square.

422
00:51:55,840 --> 00:52:00,500
Connect those dots and see what new shape
is revealed.

423
00:52:10,380 --> 00:52:13,560
Connecting only the adjacent dots.

424
00:52:17,100 --> 00:52:23,280
And with this new shape, find the midpoint
of each new line.

425
00:52:32,200 --> 00:52:41,420
And connect those new dots, the adjacent
ones.

426
00:52:45,330 --> 00:52:50,870
Let that go, move into the aspect of
Chitta or memory.

427
00:52:56,590 --> 00:53:00,750
Go back to the moment of waking up this
morning.

428
00:53:06,170 --> 00:53:10,070
Recall the first sensation that woke you
up.

429
00:53:13,290 --> 00:53:17,650
And begin to play through the day up until
this moment now.

430
00:53:25,190 --> 00:53:31,070
The major moments of the day.

431
00:53:37,460 --> 00:53:42,520
Be aware at which points there are gaps
and which points are vivid.

432
00:53:51,220 --> 00:53:56,540
Remain internally aware and awake with
review of the day.

433
00:54:16,350 --> 00:54:22,250
If the mind engages or gets distracted,
come back to the review.

434
00:54:29,670 --> 00:54:38,470
If you finish the review, go back and add
details.

435
00:54:44,150 --> 00:54:47,000
Letting that go, we now move into
Ahamkara.

436
00:54:54,460 --> 00:55:01,100
Imagine that your life is divided into
four parts, your age divided by four.

437
00:55:05,080 --> 00:55:09,100
What were you like in your first stage of
life, in your first quarter?

438
00:55:17,160 --> 00:55:19,980
Your personality, your dreams.

439
00:55:25,580 --> 00:55:29,560
What do you remember about yourself in the
first quarter of life?

440
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:37,200
That feeling of being you.

441
00:55:43,890 --> 00:55:46,790
Now move into the second quarter of your
life.

442
00:55:50,350 --> 00:55:53,510
What new identity emerged?

443
00:55:56,310 --> 00:56:03,090
How did the views of the world change
based on these new experiences?

444
00:56:15,340 --> 00:56:21,380
Move into the third portion of life.

445
00:56:21,840 --> 00:56:25,760
What was the sense of self at this stage?

446
00:56:30,180 --> 00:56:35,640
Did the personality or self-identity take
new forms?

447
00:56:42,080 --> 00:56:48,100
And finally, what is your idea of yourself
in this current stage of life?

448
00:56:56,820 --> 00:57:01,880
What has been the transformation of the
ego from that first stage?

449
00:57:09,700 --> 00:57:12,480
What aspects of you remain?

450
00:57:12,620 --> 00:57:16,340
What aspects of you have completely
emerged?

451
00:57:22,800 --> 00:57:24,680
Or fallen away?

452
00:57:34,090 --> 00:57:37,570
We now rotate our awareness through the
deep psyche.

453
00:57:45,170 --> 00:57:48,670
Bring the awareness into the region of the
pelvic floor.

454
00:57:53,990 --> 00:57:55,370
Muladhara chakra.

455
00:57:57,310 --> 00:58:00,130
Security and basic needs.

456
00:58:04,250 --> 00:58:10,050
The pelvic region around the base of the
spine and pubic bone.

457
00:58:15,010 --> 00:58:17,830
Joy and fulfillment of karmas.

458
00:58:25,210 --> 00:58:28,610
Healthy sexuality and creativity.

459
00:58:33,230 --> 00:58:36,890
The area of the abdomen around the navel.

460
00:58:41,990 --> 00:58:44,450
Willpower, ego, identity.

461
00:58:49,650 --> 00:58:55,010
The region of the heart around the
sternum.

462
00:58:58,090 --> 00:59:01,850
Community, generosity and deep feeling.

463
00:59:06,150 --> 00:59:12,570
The area around the base of the throat.

464
00:59:13,470 --> 00:59:15,790
Transformation and purification.

465
00:59:19,530 --> 00:59:23,530
The area of the head around the eyebrow
center.

466
00:59:27,150 --> 00:59:30,230
Intuition, wisdom and guidance.

467
00:59:35,910 --> 00:59:39,190
The area at the top of the head.

468
00:59:43,370 --> 00:59:48,630
A sense of total integration between all
other dimensions.

469
00:59:57,140 --> 01:00:01,840
Have a sense of your awareness and state
of consciousness as it is now.

470
01:00:11,400 --> 01:00:19,250
Is it predominantly in any one kosha?

471
01:00:25,050 --> 01:00:26,670
The physical body.

472
01:00:28,110 --> 01:00:29,670
Energetic body.

473
01:00:31,310 --> 01:00:32,710
Mental dimension.

474
01:00:35,910 --> 01:00:38,530
Intuitive or psychic dimension.

475
01:00:41,250 --> 01:00:47,630
Or some subtler aspect of consciousness.

476
01:00:53,270 --> 01:01:02,010
Look into the space behind the forehead,
the mental screen.

477
01:01:05,150 --> 01:01:10,270
Notice anything that may be arising in
that area.

478
01:01:19,910 --> 01:01:23,890
Any color, any darkness or light.

479
01:01:27,350 --> 01:01:29,810
Memories or inner dialogue.

480
01:01:34,170 --> 01:01:39,690
Watch them like clouds, giving them
permission to change and move.

481
01:01:47,220 --> 01:01:52,360
And finally move down into the heart space
around the chest.

482
01:01:59,560 --> 01:02:02,960
Checking in if you feel anything there.

483
01:02:07,300 --> 01:02:13,940
It can be physical sensations or energetic
sensations.

484
01:02:15,540 --> 01:02:17,140
Actual emotions.

485
01:02:21,820 --> 01:02:27,560
Begin to breathe more deeply so you feel
this area of the chest expand and

486
01:02:27,560 --> 01:02:28,180
contract.

487
01:02:42,840 --> 01:02:48,500
Take progressively longer breaths so that
the abdomen is involved as well.

488
01:02:54,320 --> 01:03:02,880
Begin to externalize the senses such as
awareness of sounds.

489
01:03:07,830 --> 01:03:10,100
Sounds from all directions.

490
01:03:12,920 --> 01:03:15,640
Sensations of touch from below and above.

491
01:03:22,440 --> 01:03:25,200
Awareness of smells coming in with each
breath.

492
01:03:30,120 --> 01:03:34,540
Visualize where you are in the room and
features of the room.

493
01:03:42,540 --> 01:03:45,980
And know that this practice has come to an
end.

494
01:03:51,300 --> 01:03:56,880
Begin to bring movements into your fingers
and toes.

495
01:03:57,500 --> 01:03:58,980
Wrists and ankles.

496
01:04:01,280 --> 01:04:02,000
Neck and head.

497
01:04:03,860 --> 01:04:10,100
Give yourself a long stretch like you are
waking up in the morning with a breath in.

498
01:04:15,260 --> 01:04:18,020
Then exhale and hug your knees into your
chest.

499
01:04:22,360 --> 01:04:25,360
Rocking from side to side, massaging the
back.

500
01:04:31,240 --> 01:04:35,500
And over the next minute, find your way
back to sitting.

501
01:04:43,080 --> 01:04:46,460
Keeping your eyes closed if you are
comfortable to do so.

502
01:04:51,240 --> 01:04:57,840
And remain in a state of stillness for a
few moments longer.

503
01:05:21,740 --> 01:05:27,220
In which dimension does your awareness
naturally settle?

504
01:05:48,100 --> 01:05:54,220
Bring the hands into pranam mudra.

505
01:05:54,540 --> 01:05:56,620
Move into a vigorous round of palming.

506
01:06:02,740 --> 01:06:05,580
Trying to make the hands very hot.

507
01:06:09,680 --> 01:06:12,240
And then bringing that heat to the covered
eyes.

508
01:06:17,240 --> 01:06:21,380
Connect with the sensations of pressure
and heat.

509
01:06:25,180 --> 01:06:27,480
Inhale that warmth back into yourself.

510
01:06:33,460 --> 01:06:38,380
And exhaling, lower the hands.

511
01:06:40,760 --> 01:06:44,640
We are going to take a five minute break.

512
01:06:47,760 --> 01:06:52,860
Try and keep it at five minutes if
possible.

513
01:06:53,120 --> 01:06:57,480
And then we will come back to a few spinal
loosening practices and one short

514
01:06:57,480 --> 01:06:58,040
pranayama.

515
01:06:58,420 --> 01:07:01,820
And then go into the more theoretical
concepts.

516
01:07:48,930 --> 01:07:50,110
Okay, stay on still.

517
01:14:18,370 --> 01:14:34,010
We are going to do some standing practices
just to give our spine a break.

518
01:14:35,210 --> 01:14:39,990
If you have never done these practices
before, they will serve you for a

519
01:14:39,990 --> 01:14:40,510
lifetime.

520
01:14:46,370 --> 01:14:51,330
The spine, if you look in yoga,
the spine is the pathway that you find

521
01:14:51,330 --> 01:14:56,330
from Hatha Yoga all the way to Kundalini
Yoga.

522
01:15:01,370 --> 01:15:05,470
So it's used in every single branch from
gross to subtle.

523
01:15:13,330 --> 01:15:21,330
Like that point from earlier, it requires
millions of connections to really get into

524
01:15:21,330 --> 01:15:22,650
a part of ourselves.

525
01:15:25,390 --> 01:15:34,050
I highly recommend as many spinal
awareness practices as you can in your

526
01:15:34,050 --> 01:15:34,570
lifetime.

527
01:15:43,950 --> 01:15:48,930
Because ultimately we want to be able to
follow a single atom from the base all the

528
01:15:48,930 --> 01:15:50,530
way to the brain itself.

529
01:15:59,550 --> 01:16:02,590
Feet together, hands interlaced on top.

530
01:16:07,030 --> 01:16:10,590
Inhale as you stretch upwards and down the
walls.

531
01:16:14,150 --> 01:16:15,490
Exhale, lowering.

532
01:16:16,630 --> 01:16:18,070
Four more times in.

533
01:16:19,810 --> 01:16:21,630
Hold for a few moments.

534
01:16:23,930 --> 01:16:24,590
Exhale.

535
01:16:25,690 --> 01:16:26,630
Three on your own.

536
01:16:29,770 --> 01:16:35,710
Keep the awareness in the spine and on
deep breathing.

537
01:16:49,790 --> 01:16:53,670
When finished, separate the feet out,
shoulder-width apart.

538
01:16:58,230 --> 01:17:00,570
Palms flipped upwards.

539
01:17:02,310 --> 01:17:03,450
Deep breath in.

540
01:17:04,390 --> 01:17:06,430
Exhaling, bend to one side.

541
01:17:08,810 --> 01:17:11,910
Notice what you feel and where you feel
it.

542
01:17:15,750 --> 01:17:17,750
Inhale centered and exhale opposite.

543
01:17:20,090 --> 01:17:21,710
Inhale up, that's one round.

544
01:17:23,350 --> 01:17:24,550
Two out.

545
01:17:26,650 --> 01:17:26,990
In.

546
01:17:28,090 --> 01:17:28,890
Out.

547
01:17:30,850 --> 01:17:31,610
In.

548
01:17:31,930 --> 01:17:33,290
Three more on your own.

549
01:17:37,990 --> 01:17:40,990
If you can, even visualize the bend.

550
01:17:46,510 --> 01:17:50,470
Imagine that your breath is what initiates
movement.

551
01:17:56,590 --> 01:17:58,870
And remain connected to the actual

552
01:18:04,510 --> 01:18:06,250
sensations in the spine.

553
01:18:08,970 --> 01:18:12,550
When you finish the three rounds,
you can lower the hands.

554
01:18:17,210 --> 01:18:20,050
The next round requires the arms being
out.

555
01:18:20,290 --> 01:18:21,750
We're in a tight space.

556
01:18:27,910 --> 01:18:38,070
You can even put your arms around like
you're hugging yourself.

557
01:18:41,450 --> 01:18:43,010
Just don't karate chop your neighbor.

558
01:18:47,110 --> 01:18:50,150
You're going to twist to the left,
pushing on the left shoulder.

559
01:18:53,910 --> 01:18:55,350
Inhale to center.

560
01:18:57,210 --> 01:18:59,450
Exhale, twist to the right, push on the
right.

561
01:19:01,950 --> 01:19:02,830
Inhale, center.

562
01:19:04,050 --> 01:19:04,990
Exhale, left.

563
01:19:06,710 --> 01:19:07,790
Inhale, center.

564
01:19:08,810 --> 01:19:09,810
Exhale, right.

565
01:19:11,030 --> 01:19:11,830
Inhale, center.

566
01:19:11,990 --> 01:19:12,970
Three more on your own.

567
01:19:28,720 --> 01:19:31,680
When finished, come on the hands and
knees.

568
01:19:37,860 --> 01:19:41,940
We do a few rounds of the cat pose.

569
01:19:46,200 --> 01:19:50,440
If you know it, you can begin,
otherwise we describe one round.

570
01:19:54,560 --> 01:19:56,680
Exhaling, arch up, chin down.

571
01:20:01,880 --> 01:20:04,560
Inhale, curve down, chin up.

572
01:20:09,180 --> 01:20:11,120
Exhaling, round the spine up.

573
01:20:15,300 --> 01:20:16,800
Inhaling, curve down.

574
01:20:19,400 --> 01:20:20,420
Three more on your own.

575
01:20:22,640 --> 01:20:25,860
Don't just do the movements, feel the
movements.

576
01:20:30,280 --> 01:20:35,000
Is there any part of the spine you do not
feel, or that you feel acutely?

577
01:20:53,300 --> 01:20:58,100
When finished with five rounds,
come to sit on the heels if okay for your

578
01:20:58,100 --> 01:21:00,420
knees, otherwise a cross-legged posture.

579
01:21:00,420 --> 01:21:17,240
Hands resting on the thighs or lap.

580
01:21:17,660 --> 01:21:20,640
Awareness at the entrance of the nasal
passages.

581
01:21:24,440 --> 01:21:31,120
By feeling the force coming in and out of
each nostril, estimate which one is

582
01:21:31,120 --> 01:21:32,740
breathing more strongly.

583
01:21:47,600 --> 01:21:50,960
This is called Suara Dominance.

584
01:21:56,840 --> 01:22:01,420
It tends to fluctuate every 60 to 80
minutes.

585
01:22:08,220 --> 01:22:17,320
It is an indicator of which nervous system
is more active.

586
01:22:20,300 --> 01:22:26,820
We are going to use one of the most
beneficial and gentle pranayamas for

587
01:22:26,820 --> 01:22:28,240
bringing it towards balance.

588
01:22:29,040 --> 01:22:35,720
We are going to do one of the simplest and
most elementary pranayamas to achieve a

589
01:22:35,720 --> 01:22:36,920
balance between the two forces.

590
01:22:36,920 --> 01:22:40,980
We are going to imagine inhaling through
the left to eyebrow center,

591
01:22:46,880 --> 01:22:49,420
exhaling down the right,

592
01:22:55,020 --> 01:22:58,300
then inhaling back up the right to eyebrow
center,

593
01:23:01,640 --> 01:23:03,040
exhaling down the left.

594
01:23:07,120 --> 01:23:12,620
So you are always inhaling from one side
but exhaling from the other.

595
01:23:16,860 --> 01:23:21,540
And then inhaling from that other side and
exhaling from the first.

596
01:23:31,060 --> 01:23:36,040
Continue some rounds of alternate nostril
breathing.

597
01:23:50,260 --> 01:23:56,340
This is an ideal pranayama to do between
any transition in the day.

598
01:24:03,900 --> 01:24:16,760
Arriving home from work, preparing to go
to sleep, even waking up in the morning.

599
01:24:18,940 --> 01:24:30,560
The breath is as silent as possible,
at the same time as long and deep as

600
01:24:30,560 --> 01:24:34,180
possible.

601
01:24:34,180 --> 01:24:39,880
So in the same way that you are balancing
the two nostrils,

602
01:24:44,560 --> 01:24:48,980
it is also a balance between effort of
breathing and depth of breathing.

603
01:24:48,980 --> 01:25:09,410
Next time you exhale, start to breathe in
equally from both.

604
01:25:15,770 --> 01:25:21,250
Each breath in merges at the eyebrow
center, each breath out splits and flows

605
01:25:21,250 --> 01:25:22,970
out equally.

606
01:25:22,970 --> 01:25:34,990
Bring the

607
01:25:41,930 --> 01:26:00,500
hands into pranamudra, move into a round
of palming, cover the eyes, gaze into the

608
01:26:00,500 --> 01:26:01,020
darkness.

609
01:26:07,380 --> 01:26:09,580
Inhale deeply into yourself,

610
01:26:13,140 --> 01:26:16,260
exhaling lower the hands and slowly open
the eyes.

611
01:26:24,100 --> 01:26:29,760
I've done two of these talks already in
Montevideo, in different venues,

612
01:26:31,000 --> 01:26:39,420
and of course they change with each time
because they're not really scripted.

613
01:26:46,080 --> 01:26:55,420
And this time I was determined to do a
little bit of practice first.

614
01:26:56,420 --> 01:27:00,460
For those of you who are yoga teachers or
practitioners,

615
01:27:05,580 --> 01:27:11,160
there's always value in hearing something
being done slightly differently.

616
01:27:18,620 --> 01:27:21,760
Especially if you feel like you know the
practice.

617
01:27:26,240 --> 01:27:31,640
It's very easy to slip into a routine
where something works and so you just

618
01:27:31,640 --> 01:27:33,280
deliver it the same forever.

619
01:27:40,500 --> 01:27:48,020
I think that's great, but then we risk
plateauing our own knowledge and how to

620
01:27:48,020 --> 01:27:51,400
engage with those in front of us,
including ourselves.

621
01:28:02,080 --> 01:28:15,620
And for those of you who may not be
familiar with some of these practices,

622
01:28:16,400 --> 01:28:21,000
I think it's harder to find them online
whereas the information is abundant.

623
01:28:22,460 --> 01:28:23,740
It's hard, isn't it?

624
01:28:23,880 --> 01:28:29,340
To find the practices online.

625
01:28:35,800 --> 01:28:40,140
First idea is things that are gross and
things that are subtle.

626
01:28:45,300 --> 01:28:50,580
There's an aspect of reality that's
available to our five senses and there's

627
01:28:50,580 --> 01:28:56,860
an entire aspect of reality that isn't
accessible by our senses.

628
01:29:06,220 --> 01:29:09,160
Or at least our external senses.

629
01:29:11,680 --> 01:29:15,400
And yet most of us would agree that if we
were to suddenly become blind,

630
01:29:15,580 --> 01:29:16,640
we're still a person.

631
01:29:22,320 --> 01:29:23,740
We have a sense of self, right?

632
01:29:25,800 --> 01:29:28,560
So now cut out a secondary sensation.

633
01:29:28,740 --> 01:29:30,720
Now we can't hear as well.

634
01:29:34,720 --> 01:29:36,120
Still a person or not?

635
01:29:38,920 --> 01:29:42,140
What if we cut out all the five external
senses?

636
01:29:46,480 --> 01:29:52,100
Maybe an altered sense of reality,
but we can imagine we'd still have a sense

637
01:29:52,100 --> 01:29:53,080
of...

638
01:29:53,080 --> 01:29:55,260
I'm here, don't kill me, right?

639
01:30:01,080 --> 01:30:05,300
This is a really interesting topic in the
world of coma patients.

640
01:30:09,880 --> 01:30:14,580
Sometimes no real sign of life other than
some brainwave activity.

641
01:30:21,740 --> 01:30:26,000
And yet we've had people come out of
really long comas and say, No,

642
01:30:26,100 --> 01:30:28,260
I was having an inner experience,
I was there.

643
01:30:35,680 --> 01:30:39,740
And all of us experience that even in
states of deep sleep.

644
01:30:44,260 --> 01:30:51,000
We're not there, but through some training
we can progressively develop a sense of,

645
01:30:51,460 --> 01:30:52,420
I'm somewhere.

646
01:31:00,540 --> 01:31:06,580
Even with the physical body, you can start
to cut off limbs, but as long as the

647
01:31:06,580 --> 01:31:11,880
spinal cord, a few vital organs in the
brain are intact, And the same thing

648
01:31:11,880 --> 01:31:12,680
happens with the physical body.

649
01:31:12,860 --> 01:31:19,240
We can remove some parts, amputate,
but leaving behind some important organs,

650
01:31:19,560 --> 01:31:22,940
we still have the sensation of existing.

651
01:31:30,900 --> 01:31:34,660
As if the vital force continues to
maintain a force of consciousness and

652
01:31:34,660 --> 01:31:36,320
vitality, a sensation.

653
01:31:45,380 --> 01:31:51,400
There are yogis who are aware of this,
and when they say yogi, they mean anyone

654
01:31:51,400 --> 01:31:55,060
who has the consciousness to explore the
inner world.

655
01:32:00,360 --> 01:32:05,180
And when he uses the word yoga,
he does not speak exclusively of Indian

656
01:32:05,180 --> 01:32:05,180
thought.

657
01:32:09,720 --> 01:32:16,100
He is preserving and evolving these
aspects of self-exploration.

658
01:32:26,320 --> 01:32:32,020
But yoga and tantra as a search for
universal patterns,

659
01:32:36,600 --> 01:32:44,460
is not distinct to India, and no one has a
claim on it.

660
01:32:47,100 --> 01:32:53,760
So the yogis who observe that you can cut
away aspects of at least these three

661
01:32:53,760 --> 01:33:01,200
layers, So we can cut away the aspects of
these three layers.

662
01:33:01,880 --> 01:33:04,080
Physical to mental.

663
01:33:14,960 --> 01:33:20,020
And removing these layers, we can ask
ourselves, at what point do we stop being

664
01:33:20,020 --> 01:33:20,300
us?

665
01:33:24,320 --> 01:33:28,530
It is very difficult, because no one wants
to die doing this process.

666
01:33:33,620 --> 01:33:38,740
Many people have given up their lives
trying to transmit this.

667
01:33:38,860 --> 01:33:43,720
All of the gurus have sat in between fires
for multiple years.

668
01:33:54,700 --> 01:33:57,140
That practice is known to kill people.

669
01:33:57,260 --> 01:34:00,700
That's one of the last practices for a
number of yogis.

670
01:34:06,220 --> 01:34:07,860
Because it's extreme.

671
01:34:09,200 --> 01:34:15,900
It's extreme physically, it's extreme
energetically, it's extreme mentally.

672
01:34:19,240 --> 01:34:22,780
And the idea is one, is to burn karma
through that austerity.

673
01:34:27,560 --> 01:34:33,900
But the second is, through that stress,
to force oneself into the most subtle

674
01:34:33,900 --> 01:34:35,780
cracks of consciousness.

675
01:34:47,300 --> 01:34:52,700
In the physical dimension, I only listed a
few, but you can imagine that there are

676
01:34:52,700 --> 01:34:53,260
many more.

677
01:34:54,320 --> 01:34:59,280
In the physical dimension, I only listed a
few, but you can imagine that there are

678
01:34:59,280 --> 01:34:59,960
many more.

679
01:35:00,380 --> 01:35:11,360
And he says that all the things that I
have put there, in the physical body,

680
01:35:11,700 --> 01:35:15,920
are superimposed with the energetic part
and with the mental part.

681
01:35:15,920 --> 01:35:20,040
And that the heart, for example,
will not beat, that I'm aware of,

682
01:35:20,120 --> 01:35:21,340
without a functioning brain.

683
01:35:29,780 --> 01:35:35,760
But just entertain me for a moment and
imagine what I mean by physical really

684
01:35:35,760 --> 01:35:37,860
means physical.

685
01:35:46,160 --> 01:35:46,800
Imagine that...

686
01:35:49,000 --> 01:35:52,300
Imagine that the physical part,
for a moment, is only the physical part,

687
01:35:52,300 --> 01:35:53,700
only the physical part of the body.

688
01:35:56,000 --> 01:35:57,660
As if it were the brick of that wall.

689
01:36:10,500 --> 01:36:15,920
So the energetic part is the part that
permeates that physical part.

690
01:36:19,860 --> 01:36:25,080
So it can navigate or dive into that
physical part.

691
01:36:25,080 --> 01:36:32,460
And if you study cell biology and the
biological chemical reactions within,

692
01:36:38,280 --> 01:36:41,080
energy has evolved to both flow

693
01:36:47,840 --> 01:36:51,060
